D.\nBUCHANAN. Nov. II. \u2014The Coro\nner's jury impaneled to hold the in\nqu. over (he mutilated body of Sid\nney Pope, a young white man. found i\n<\u00bbn the Central of Georgia Railway'\ntrack a few miles south of here, ad i\njourned until Thursday to continue\nthe investigation. j\n111 80M10NTH5\nHU MEET HEBE\nI J\nChamber of Commerce Head to\nWelcome Delegates at Recep\ntion at the Ansley.\nA hundred members of the South-\nI em Homeopathic Medical Society be\ngan a three days' session at 10 o\u2019clock\nTuesday morning in the ballroom at\nthe Hotel Ansley and took up as j\ni their flrst business the election of\nofficers for the ensuing year. At the\nopening of the assembly, the officers\nwere TV. B. Loraine, of Richmond,\npresident: Dr .j. E. Koons, of Dan\nville, first vice presidejit; Dr. J. B.\nGriffin, of St. Augustine, second vice\npresident: Dr. M. A. Newman, of\nNorfolk, treasurer: and Dr. Lee Nor\nman, of Louisville, secretary.\nThe visiting delegates will be offi-\ncially welcomed to the city Tuesday\nnigiit by Wilmer L. Moore, of the\nAtlanta Chamber of Commerce, at a\nreception in the ballroom of the Hotel t\nAnsley. Dr. Loe Monroe, of Miami.)\nwill respond.\nThe convention will be in session\nthrougli Thursday. No clinics will\nbe attended, but the meetings will be\ndevoted to the exchange of views and\nplans for a more compact organiza\ntion, and general progress, profes\nsionally and from a business stand-\npoint.\nEscapes Just After\nHis Plea of Guilty\n(.\u2019LI AIBLS Nov. '.\u2014Roscoe\nHuff, who had just entered a plea of\nguilty a charge of bringing \u00abi lo\nyear-old girl to Columbus from Shaw\nmut. Ala., and passing her as his wife,\nescaped from Cue Sheriff\u2019s office w) i>\ncourt was in\nA number of persons were in the\noffice and Huff walked out with the\ncrovtd.\nSquare Deal Coffee is\neverything its name im\nplies. Roasted daily and\n,J>lended in Atlanta.\nSPECIALPRICE\nWith One Heading of Either Hearst s American or The Atl